The paper deals with radio resource allocation in a cloud-radio access network (C-RAN) using sparse code multiple access (SCMA) technology. This involves optimizing the allocation of radio resources to different slices while considering uncertain channel state information (CSI) and various constraints. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer engineering (cs.CE).
